Question 3

Which event seems most directly connected to Brent Oil prices? Explain why.

Expected Output: Short Paragraph Linked to One Chart

The Hormuz Strait crisis and related energy supply disruptions appear to be most directly connected to Brent Oil prices. Since a large share of global crude oil trade passes through this region, geopolitical tensions can create concerns about supply shortages and lead to higher oil prices. This relationship is reflected in Figure 1 (Brent Crude Oil Price Trend) from Part I, where periods of volatility correspond to supply-side uncertainties.
